Description:
COMPANY

REI Network is the brand name conceived by “PLENA Gestão de Projetos e Empreendimentos de Engenharia LTDA”,  to put together successful professionals and entrepreneurs interested in profiting with the development of real estate projects, via research, assessment, planning and development of business opportunities aiming surpass profit targets expected by its clients. 

OPORTUNITIES 

The best way to invest in real estate is to participate in professionally managed development projects.

Only through detailed and precise financial planning, market research and proper legal structuring, you will be able to minimize your risk and leverage your profit potential accordingly 

Do not invest in real estate, invest in property developments with the right support of qualified professionals form REI in the areas of:  

- Technical:  architecture, urban planning and engineering;

- Commercial: market research, marketing planning, sales management;

- Financial: budget, feasibility studies, profitability management;

- Legal: documentation, contracts, real estate registrations;

- Fiscal: fiscal planning and accounting; 

- Management: comprehensive project management.

Elite Capital Asset Management S.A. est une société de gestion de portefeuille agréée par la Commission de Surveillance des Marchés Financiers (COSUMAF) en date du 28 juillet 2021 pour exercer sur le Marché Financier de l'Afrique Centrale (CEMAC).

Notre agrément est enregistré sous la référence: COSUMAF-SGP-02/2021.

Notre objet social:
- la promotion et la gestion des FCP, des FCPE et SICAV;
- la création et la gestion des fonds d'investissement;
- le private banking;
- la prise de participation

Toutes opérations financières, commerciales, mobilières et immobilières se rattachant directement ou indirectement à l'objet social ou tous autres objets similaires ou connexes susceptibles d'en faciliter l'application ou le développement.

Born in 1924, Nevzat Özgörkey, one of Turkey's most prestigious and respectable entrepreneurs, established four Coca-Cola bottling plants in the Aegean and Mediterranean regions and two in Romania from 1967 up until the formation of Özgörkey Holding in 1997. He also co-founded Ege Biracılık, Anadolu Efes's first brewery in Turkey. In 1997, he formed Özgörkey Holding with his sons Cemal and Armağan Özgörkey.

The company is now:

*the shareholder of Coca-Cola İçecek A.Ş.; 
*the major shareholder of Hollanda Etap International Bv being an investment trust; 
*the shareholder of Anadolu Etap Tarım ve Gıda Ürünleri San. Tic. A.Ş with Anadolu Group and Brazilian Cutrale Group  on equal basis. 

Furthermore, the company is the sole owner of Etapak Printing and Packaging Industry and Commerce Inc., a solutions partner that is active in plastic, printing and packaging, as well as materials handling.

Il Gruppo Zignago è una solida realtà industriale - profondamente radicata nel territorio del Veneto - costituita da un portafoglio diversificato di aziende controllate da Zignago Holding S.p.A., società di proprietà di un ramo della famiglia Marzotto.

I principali settori merceologici sui quali opera il Gruppo sono:

VETRO – Gruppo Zignago Vetro: produzione e commercializzazione di contenitori in vetro cavo;

VINO – Santa Margherita Gruppo Vinicolo: produzione di vini di alta qualità;

ENERGIA – Zignago Power: produzione e distribuzione di energia elettrica da fonti rinnovabili;

IMMOBILIARE - Zignago Immobiliare: gestione di beni immobili;

SANIFICAZIONE E DISINFESTAZIONE ECOLOGICA – Multitecno: ricerca, sviluppo e produzione di sistemi innovativi, rispettosi dell’ambiente, per la difesa dagli animali infestanti.

La capogruppo Zignago Holding S.p.A. ha natura di holding di partecipazioni, fornisce servizi e coordinamento in ambito finanziario, amministrativo, legale, fiscale, risorse umane ed informatico per le Società controllate.

Altera offers investment products in Dutch property which are tailored to the needs and requirements of institutional investors through a structure of integrated management with letter shares in each sector.
This means, among other things:

• a structure with the advantages of unlisted indirect property and the risk/return
characteristics of direct property;
• targeted participation in specific sector portfolios (freedom of allocation);
• flexibility of entries and exits;
• no structural financing with loan capital;
• active asset management;
• no in-company project development activities;
• a multi-criterion investment objective;
• transparency in policy, processes and accountability;
• application of best practices and a high level of compliance;
• cost-efficiency (low management costs);
• investment based on a research-driven strategy;
• optimal implementation of measures to promote sustainability;
• independence, no conflicts of interest and a strong emphasis on compliance;
• customer-oriented servicing and marketing.

We aim for growth in assets under management for the benefit of existing and prospective shareholders; this also helps to improve the risk/return characteristics.
